<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="672" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/11–1449</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-14T13:00:00+08:00">November
                                    14, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 14—3:29 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>696. During past several weeks numerous unconfirmed reports have reached
                            this ConGen from diverse sources that Generalissimo was seriously
                            considering transferring his headquarters from Taipei to southwest (see
                            Hong Kong’s 1001 to Department<note n="56" xml:id="d672fn56">Not
                                printed.</note>) where he would assume active direct leadership.
                            Recent developments may, of course, have changed such plans if they did,
                            in fact, exist.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department, repeated Hong Kong 72.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Macdonald</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>